{#
  Example 06 — Follow the OS `prefers-color-scheme`.

  The macro has no opinion about light vs. dark; it just owns the
  selection contract. To make the first-visit default follow the OS,
  resolve `prefers-color-scheme` in your Nunjucks host and pass the
  resolved slug as `defaultValue`. The user can still pick anything
  they like afterwards, and the choice persists via `storageKey`.

  In Express:

      const prefersDark =
          req.headers["sec-ch-prefers-color-scheme"] === "dark";
      res.render("page.njk", { prefersDark });

  In the template, `prefersDark` is a boolean we use to pick the
  defaultValue.
#}
{% from "../theme-picker.njk" import themePicker %}

{{ themePicker({
    label: "Theme",
    themesUrl: "/assets/themes/",
    themes: ["light", "dark"],
    defaultValue: "dark" if prefersDark else "light",
    storageKey: "my-app:theme"
}) }}

<script type="module">
    import { autoInit } from "../theme-picker.client.js";
    const [controller] = autoInit();

    // Track OS preference changes live:
    if (window.matchMedia) {
        const mql = window.matchMedia("(prefers-color-scheme: dark)");
        mql.addEventListener("change", (e) => {
            controller?.setTheme(e.matches ? "dark" : "light");
        });
    }
</script>
